item.description:
V.2 provides a declarative style of configuration for I/O provisioning instead of the hard-coded approach offered in V1.
Examples of the various methods and approaches which can be used to provision the I/O needs are available in the examples project.
Properties properties = new Properties(); properties.put(&quot;id&quot;, &quot;my_digital_input&quot;); properties.put(&quot;address&quot;, DIGITAL_INPUT_PIN); properties.put(&quot;pull&quot;, &quot;UP&quot;); properties.put(&quot;name&quot;, &quot;MY-DIGITAL-INPUT&quot;); var config = DigitalInput.newConfigBuilder(pi4j) .load(properties) .build(); var input = pi4j.din().create(config);
